{% block title %}
    Air Units
{% endblock %}

{% block body %}
    <div class="alert alert-info">
        <ul>
            <li>Air units can attack and defend in territories</li>
            <li>Air units can attack in sea zones</li>
            <li>Air units stationed on Carriers can defend in sea zones</li>
            <li>Fighters and Tactical Bombers can defend an adjacent sea zone, if their territory has an operative Air Base (Scrambling)</li>
            <li>Air units can land in friendly territories (but not in just captured ones)</li>
            <li>Fighters and Tactical Bombers can land on friendly Carriers</li>
            <li>Air units can move through hostile territories and sea zones</li>
            <li>Air units can hit submarines only if a friendly destroyer is in the battle.</li>
            <li>During noncombat movement and new unit mobilization, you must provide for safe landing of as many air units as possible after all combats are resolved</li>
            <li>Air Units that cannot land during the Non-Combat-Phase are removed</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="alert alert-danger">
        You cannot deliberately send air units into combat
        situations that place them out of range of a place to land
        afterward. In the Combat Move phase, prior to rolling any
        battles, you must be able to demonstrate some possible
        way (however remote the possibility is) for all your
        attacking air units to land safely that turn
    </div>
    {% import 'AppBundle:Macro:button_collapse.html.twig' as buttonCollapse %}
    {{ buttonCollapse.create('unit_air_units_fighter', 'Fighter', block('fighter')) }}
    {{ buttonCollapse.create('unit_air_units_tactical_bomber', 'Tactical Bomber', block('tactical_bomber')) }}
    {{ buttonCollapse.create('unit_air_units_strategic_bomber', 'Strategic Bomber', block('strategic_bomber')) }}
{% endblock %}

{% block fighter %}
    <table class="table table-bordered">
        <tr>
            <td><strong>Cost</strong></td>
            <td>10</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <strong>Attack</strong>
            </td>
            <td>3</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <strong>Defense</strong>
            </td>
            <td>4</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <strong>Move</strong>
            </td>
            <td>4</td>
        </tr>
    </table>
    <h5>Unit Characteristics</h5>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Carrier Operations: </strong>can land on and take off from a friendly carrier</li>
        <li><strong>Fighter Escorts: </strong> can participate in strategic and tactical bombing raids as escort to defend the Bombers from intercepting Fighters</li>
        <li><strong>Fighter Interceptors: </strong> can defend against a strategic and tactical bombing raids when they are in the territory that is to be bombed</li>
        <li><strong>Air Superiority: </strong> Raises the attack of a Tactical Bomber to 4 when paired
    </ul>
{% endblock %}

{% block tactical_bomber %}
